Goodwood officials believe their summer Festival meeting will be elevated to the global racing stage after unveiling the biggest sponsorship deal in the history of British horseracing.

The 10-year agreement with the Qatar Racing and Equestrian club, which also backs Longchamp’s Prix de L’Arc de Triomphe meeting, will see prizemoney for the 2015 five-day fixture rise to £4.5million with an injection of £2m into eight key races.

The feature Group One Sussex Stakes, won last season by Kingman and in 2011 and 2012 by the mighty Frankel, will be worth an extra £700,000 making the Group One mile contest only the sixth £1m race in the British calendar.

